The Nigerian Investment Promotion Commission (NIPC) is set to unveil over 100 investment projects available in Nigeria to investors all over the world. This was disclosed yesterday by the Director for Strategic Communication at the commission, Mr Emeka Offor during a visit to Media Trust Headquarters in Abuja. He said the investment openings in Nigeria would be unveiled during Nigeria’s ‘Direct Investors’ Summit’ slated to hold in Abuja from May 21 to 22. Mr Offor said the summit, tagged “Investment Meets Opportunities,” will serve as a meeting ground for investors to network, leading to strategic alliances for joint ventures.